      "end": 8.48,
      "text": "This is a Libervox recording. All Libervox recordings are in the public domain. For more",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 8.48,
      "end": 13.76,
      "text": "information, or to volunteer, please visit Libervox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 15.84,
      "end": 25.56,
      "text": "ESOPs fables. The Olive Tree and the Fig Tree. An olive tree taunted a fig tree with the",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 25.84,
      "end": 28.44,
      "text": "loss of her leaves at a certain season of the year.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 30.06,
      "end": 37.88,
      "text": "\"'You,' she said, \"'lose your leaves every autumn, and I'll dare till the spring. Whereas",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 37.88,
      "end": 44.12,
      "text": "I, as you see, remain green and flourished, all the year round.'",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 45.1,
      "end": 51.6,
      "text": "Soon afterwards there came a heavy fall of snow, which settled on the leaves of the Olive",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 51.6,
      "end": 59.64,
      "text": "so that she bent and broke under the weight. But the flakes fell harmlessly through the bare",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 59.64,
      "end": 64.78,
      "text": "branches of the fig, which survived to bear many another crop.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 67.52,
      "end": 70.62,
      "text": "End of the Olive Tree and the Fig Tree.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
